“I LOVE THIS [XBRL] SYSTEM!”

Posted on November 10, 2016 | Leave a comment


Fast turns and spot-on execution has redefined Vintage, helping us to be a top three solution in North America. Our work is highlighted every Monday in our “IPOs and Transactions of the Week” blog and email.  Importantly, our week’s success isfurther highlighted (and celebrated) by the appreciative notes our operations people receive each day from our clients.

We can’t not share the good news (anonymized for privacy). Sales can offer you full named references.
Here is just a handful of the week’s notes:
.

Kudos to our EDGAR team

Thank you all so much for all of your hard work!  Great job getting this done!
.
.


Kudos to our Typesetting team
We made today’s filing deadline with a couple minutes to spare. Well done everyone for the great teamwork to get this amendment done in an accurate and timely manner.
A sincere thank you!
.


Kudos to our EDGAR team
Our move from to Vintage was simple and our first experience was one of confidence. There were less errors/corrections than we had previously encountered [w/ other firm] and there was an attention to detail that I very much appreciated.
Since that time, we have been very pleased with our transactions and any changes we required were done in an incredibly timely fashion. In our industry, changes become necessary at the very last moment and Vintage was able to accommodate the last minute stresses very well.
.


Kudos to our Mutual Funds team
So much better! Thanks for being so proactive.
.
.


Kudos to our XBRL team
We are finished with our first draft. I have forwarded it to the accountants and attorney for comments.
.
.


Kudos to our Print team
Great. Thanks to you guys’ outstanding work!
.
.


Kudos to our EDGAR team
Thanks everyone for another successful filing! We appreciate all of the hard work and patience through our many changes.
.
